  Part B: ID_FQDN (BASIC)
     5. NUT starts to negotiate with TN1 by sending IKE_SA_INIT request.
     6. Observe the messages transmitted on Link B.
     7. After reception of IKE_SA_INIT request from the NUT, TN1 responds with an
         IKE_SA_INIT response to the NUT.
     8. Observe the messages transmitted on Link B.

=head1 Observable Result

  Part B
       Step 6: Judgment #1
       The NUT transmits an IKE_SA_INIT request including "ENCR_3DES",
       "PRF_HMAC_SHA1", "AUTH_HMAC_SHA1_96" and "D-H group 2" as proposed
       algorithms.

       Step 8: Judgment #2
       The NUT transmits an IKE_AUTH request including an ID payload which contains the value
       specified as above table.

=head1 Possible Problems

  * None.

